universe of origin : the teardown — a made machine, opened and explored
seal               : Nintendo's 64-bit machine teamed a MIPS CPU with a Silicon Graphics coprocessor that did both graphics and sound, and stuck with cartridges for speed and security. It pioneered the analog stick and rumble, and made smooth 3-D worlds — at the cost of blurry textures and tiny cartridge storage.
